<p class="Endnotes"><span id="endnote-030"><a class="_idEndnoteAnchor _idGenColorInherit" href="#endnote-030-backlink">30</a><span class="superscript CharOverride-9"> </span><span class="CharOverride-7">Dexter Filkins, &ldquo;Convoy Guards in Afghanistan Face an Inquiry,&rdquo; </span><span class="CharOverride-8">New York Times</span><span class="CharOverride-7">, June 6, 2010, available at &lt;www.nytimes.com/2010/06/07/world/asia/07convoys.html&gt;.</span></span></p>

<p class="Endnotes"><span id="endnote-031"><a class="_idEndnoteAnchor _idGenColorInherit" href="#endnote-031-backlink">31</a><span class="superscript CharOverride-9"> </span><span class="CharOverride-7">Ibid.; U.S. House of Representatives, </span><span class="CharOverride-8">Warlord, Inc</span><span class="CharOverride-7">.</span></span></p>

<p class="Endnotes"><span id="endnote-032"><a class="_idEndnoteAnchor _idGenColorInherit" href="#endnote-032-backlink">32</a><span class="superscript CharOverride-9"> </span><span class="CharOverride-7">Moshe Schwartz and Jennifer Church, </span><span class="CharOverride-8">Department of Defense&rsquo;s Use of Contractors to Support Military Operations: Background, Analysis, and Issues for Congress</span><span class="CharOverride-7">, R43074 (Washington, DC: CRS, May 17, 2013), 2. For the 2012 United Kingdom defense budget, see Christopher Chantrill, UK Public Spending Web site, available at &lt;www.ukpublicspending.co.uk/budget_current.php?title=uk_defense_budget&amp;year=2012&amp;fy=2012&amp;expand=30&gt;.</span></span></p>

